  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in Senate",
    "asOf": "2021-05-12",
    "date": "2021-06-23T20:34:13Z",
    "text": "Lifesaving Gear for Police Act\n\nThis bill invalidates any regulation, rule, guidance, recommendation, or policy issued on or after May 15, 2015, that limits the sale or donation of excess federal property to state and local law enforcement agencies unless it is enacted by Congress.\n\nAdditionally, it prohibits the use of federal funds to implement such regulation, rule, guidance, recommendation, or policy.\n\nProperty that was recalled or seized on or after May 15, 2015, must be returned, replaced, or reissued to the state or local law enforcement agency."
  },
